   <b>OBJECTIVE</b>

   </br>A Systems/Network Administrator is responsible for the health and
   welfare of the Company's systems infrastructure. Nevo is continually
   developing new applications on a variety of platforms and environments
   requiring infrastructure adjustments and accommodations. Coordinating,
   standardizing, and documenting these changes will be one of the key responsibilities
   of this position. Work will be done primarily at Nevo’s headquarters in Harvard Square,
   with occasional visits to the client site in southeast Massachusetts.
   </BR><b>This is a <i>part-time contract</i> position - up to 1-2 days per week.</b>

   <p>
   <b>MAJOR DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</b>

   <ul class="tightBodyText"><li>Reports to Chief Technology Officer

   </li><li>Creates and maintains system documentation as necessary

   </li><li>Troubleshoots, resolves, client-server software/hardware problems and creates triage processes.

   </li><li>Consolidates and assures connectivity between network domains (e.g., between Nevo and client VPNs, etc.)

   </li><li>Establishes and implements disaster recovery plans

   </li><li>Establishes and implements backup procedures and processes

   </li><li>Implements default profiles, permissions and drivers

   </li><li>Resolves cross-platform communication and conversion issues

   </li><li>Maintains and enforces standards for the Company. its usage of LAN, desktop hardware, and software products, technologies and upgrade programs.

   </li><li>Provides technical support to development staff especially when setting up project development environments.

   </li><li>Responsible for:
   <ul class="tightBodyText"><li>Security of office systems applications (e.g., web access security, account security, user privileges)
   </li><li>The integrity and security of the transfer of critical confidential data and documents.
   </li><li>Configurations, testing, upgrades and operation of systems and software within the Company.
   </ul>


   </li><li>Support and maintenance of the Company web site.

   </li><li>Plans, recommends and implements future network and server initiatives, upgrades and expansion efforts
   </li><li>Oversees equipment hardware/software inventory including MSDN subscription, site licenses, etc.
   </li></ul>

   <b>ESSENTIAL QUALIFICATIONS</b>

   <ul class="tightBodyText"><li>Bachelor's degree in Computer Science is preferred as is a MSCE.

   </li><li>Minimum 3-5 years systems administration experience with multiple platforms (PCs running Windows NT/2000/2003/XP).

   </li><li>Networking experience required (TCP/IP and client/server architecture, VPNs, etc.)

   </li><li>Strong organizational skills, attention to detail; proven problem solving and team leadership skills; proven ability to learn quickly while applying knowledge effectively

   </li><li>Strong understanding of software development environments and development process and delivery, especially rapid, iterative software development approaches

   </li><li>Comfortable in a multi-task, deadline-oriented environment

   </li><li>Excellent English written and verbal communication and interpersonal skills with an appreciation for and ability to communicate with and respond to the needs of diverse audiences.
   </li></ul>

   <b>ADDITIONAL CONSIDERATIONS</b>

   <ul class="tightBodyText"><li>Nevo will consider only direct applications by principals

   </li><li>No relocation benefits are available for this position
   </li><li>All applicabts must be able to demonstrate authorization to work in
   the United States by their start date.
   </li></ul>

